{"build_type":"library","description":"Iterate a directory's {name,type} entry list (struct-linked list, walked by .next) and emit one flat row {d:depth, t:type, n:name, s:size?, m:mode?, l:symlink?} per entry into the g_tree_out global array. BUDGET-GATED: before each row it reads g_tree_emitted vs g_tree_budget; once the count reaches the budget it sets g_tree_truncated and returns WITHOUT emitting or descending further, so a huge subtree is bounded (memory O(budget), no 120s black-box) and the caller turns g_tree_truncated into a LOUD structured output_budget_exceeded. One lstat per entry (lstat_into_shared_buffer) fills g_statbuf; size (st_size@6) added for regular files (d_type 8); mode is DEFAULT-ENCODED — perm bits (st_mode&07777,@3) added as m ONLY when they deviate from the type default (0644=420 file, 0755=493 dir); symlinks (10) carry l=target. Recurses into sub-directories (d_type 4) via walk_filesystem_tree at depth+1 (symlinks emitted not descended → no cycles); tail-recurses siblings via .next. Reuses locate_named_member_inside_mapping, build_store_path, begin_empty_mapping_document_value, add_number_to_object, add_str_field, lstat_into_shared_buffer, readlink_target_into_string, attach_named_member_inside_mapping, append_element_extending_document_sequence, walk_filesystem_tree.","module_name":"generate-flattened-directory-records-representing-entries","package_name":"generate-flattened-directory-records-representing-entries","module_globals":[{"global_name":"g_tree_out","global_type":"i64","global_init":"0"},{"global_name":"g_tree_budget","global_type":"i64","global_init":"0"},{"global_name":"g_tree_emitted","global_type":"i64","global_init":"0"},{"global_name":"g_tree_truncated","global_type":"i64","global_init":"0"}],"function_definitions":{"generate-flattened-directory-records-representing-entries":{"return_type":"i64","parameter_definitions":[{"parameter_name":"node","parameter_type":"i64"},{"parameter_name":"dir_path","parameter_type":"i64"},{"